# Festag — light-mode CTAs stay light

Do **not** use black or near-black filled primary buttons in light (or read / pure-light) mode.

## Light / read / pure-light

Auth Weiter, SSO, popup, and other primary CTAs must be **white or light fills** with **dark text**.

Canonical Linear recipe (also on `.al-root` / `:root` as `--festag-btn-dark-*`):

```css
--festag-btn-dark-bg: #ffffff;
--festag-btn-dark-bg-hover: #fafafa;
--festag-btn-dark-bg-active: #f4f4f5;
--festag-btn-dark-fg: #1e1e20;
--festag-btn-dark-fg-hover: #1e1e20;
--festag-btn-dark-fg-active: #1e1e20;
--festag-btn-dark-border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);          /* soft hairline */
--festag-btn-dark-border-hover: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.09);
--festag-btn-dark-border-active: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.09);
--festag-btn-dark-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); /* bottom only */
--festag-btn-dark-shadow-hover: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.07);
--festag-btn-dark-shadow-active: 0 1px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04); /* no inset top */
```

Hardcoded light fallbacks must match (`#ffffff` / `#1e1e20` + soft hairline + bottom shadow), not `#1e1e20` fills with `#fafafa` text.

Bad in light:
- Solid `#000` / `#0f0f10` / `#1e1e20` / `#111` filled CTAs
- Borderless white-on-white (invisible edge)
- Dual/heavy marketing shadows (`0 1px 0 …, 0 1px 3px …`)
- Inset top highlights that read as a strong upper stroke
- “Ready” Weiter that flips to a black pill while the page is still light
- Light-mode `--btn-prim` / `--festag-btn-dark-bg` set to near-black

## Dark / classic-dark

Solid black or near-black filled CTAs are allowed **only** here (or cool-slate lifts already used on OLED). Do not copy those fills into light theme tokens or light-only CSS fallbacks.

## When touching CTAs

- Theme via `--festag-btn-dark-*` / `--btn-prim*` so light and dark stay correct
- Apple/Google branded SSO may keep their brand fills; generic Weiter / primary / popup CTAs follow this rule
- When fixing existing light black pills, restore white/light fills — do not reintroduce near-black primaries in light
- See also `festag-auth-no-field-borders.mdc` for the auth Linear lock
